<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-600-561  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 600 561.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Electronic Learning  Nov-Dec 1990 v10 n3 p16(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Long-range planning. (the Bellevue, WA, School District'ssuccessful long-range technology plan; includes related articledetailing steps for creating such a plan)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Solomon, Gwen.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The Bellevue, WA, School District technology task force annuallyrefines a long-range technology plan that incorporates technologywith other educational areas, including school-based management,cooperative learning, multiage groups and curricular reform.andP;  Thefoundation of the plan is the creation of integrated technologyclassrooms (ITCs) in which technology is used for cooperativeprojects and problem solving supporting the district'slanguage-instruction, hands-on science and general problem-solvingphilosophy and strategies.andP;  There are now 23 ITC classes.andP;  Eachschool in the district is developing an individual long-rangetechnology plan.andP;  The district spends $1.3 million annually ontechnology.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Planning ApplicationsCase StudyTechnologyImplementationEducational technology.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>